text.data-name: Jade Agencies provide effective, research-driven strategies for Australian businesses looking to enter the Chinese market. As the Chinese middle class evolves and the market matures, Australian products are finding a niche in their respective industries.
text.tspan: Jade Agencies provide effective, research-driven strategies for Australian businesses looking to enter the Chinese
As the Chinese middle class evolves and the market matures, Australian products are finding a niche in their
respective industries. Healthcare, food supplements, and organic products such as skincare or honey have all achieved
great success in marketing themselves to a Chinese audience and growing their brand overseas.
The success stories, however, fail to mention the difficulties associated with breaking into the market. The Chinese
way of conducting business has long been obscure and opaque to those wishing to engage with the region.
Because of this difficulty, many Australian products that already have a cult following in China are unwilling or unable
to take advantage of market momentum. The daigou phenomenon illustrates a clear need for Australian companies to
understand, engage with, and grow alongside Chinas massive middle class.
Jade Agencies are well placed to provide advice, not just on marketing, but also on business structure and strategies
that can help your product gain the exposure it deserves in China and abroad.
